article.headline: Rider 75, Delaware 72
article.story: LAWRENCEVILLE, N.J. (AP) -- Steve Castleberry and Jerry Johnson scored 18 points each to lead Rider to a 75-72 victory over Delaware on Saturday. Castleberry led the Broncs (5-2) with seven rebounds while Johnson led all players with seven assists. Mike Ames paced Delaware (5-2) with 14 points, giving him 1000 points for his career. He also led his team with six assists. Rider's Paul Johnson came off the bench to score 11 points and grab five rebounds in 22 minutes of play. Delaware led 31-30 at the half and then went on a 10-4 scoring run at the start of the second half. Rider shot 56 percent from the field in the second half, outscoring Delaware 45-41 for the half. Ames hit two foul shots to narrow Rider's lead to four with :58 to play, but that was the closest the Blue Hens would come. Rider went 5-for-8 from the foul line in the final minute to maintain the lead.
